def subjective_value(alpha, beta, p, A, v):
    return((p - (beta * A / 2.)) * v**alpha)


def cost(theta):
    p = single_subject_data['prob']
    A = single_subject_data['ambig']
    v = single_subject_data['val']
    Y = single_subject_data['choice']
    SVl = subjective_value(theta[0], theta[1], p, A, v)
    SVf = subjective_value(theta[0], theta[1], np.ones(p.shape), np.zeros(A.shape), np.ones(p.shape) * 5)
    prob_lotto = 1/(1 + np.exp(theta[2]*(SVf - SVl)))
    #pdb.set_trace()
    prob_lotto[prob_lotto == 1] = 1 - 1e-6
    prob_lotto[prob_lotto == 0] = 1e-6
    nLL = -sum((Y * np.log(prob_lotto)) + ((1 - Y) * np.log(1 - prob_lotto)))
    return(nLL)


def model_fit(theta, data, nLL):
    LL = -nLL
    Y = data.choice
    # Rescricted Log Likelihood
    LL0 = sum(np.array(Y == 1) * np.log(.5) + ((1 - np.array(Y == 1)) * np.log(.5)))
    AIC = -2 * LL + 2 * len(theta)
    BIC = -2 * LL + np.log(len(Y)) * len(theta)
    r2 = 1 - (LL / LL0) # R^2 formula obtained by Anna confirmed with UCLA website as McDonald Psuedo R^2 formula
    return([AIC, BIC, r2])


def choice_predict(alpha, beta, gamma, p, A, v):
    SVl = subjective_value(alpha, beta, p, A, v)
    SVf = subjective_value(alpha, beta, np.ones(p.shape), np.zeros(A.shape), np.ones(p.shape) * 5)
    prob_lotto = 1/(1 + np.exp(gamma*(SVf - SVl)))
    return(prob_lotto)

# Read in the data from the expyriment
if 'long_format' in globals():
    del long_format

part_dirs = glob('../Experiment/python/data/*/')
for i, data_dir in enumerate(part_dirs):
    current_file = glob(data_dir + 'ToS_lottery*')
    x = pd.read_csv(current_file[0], comment='#', na_values='None')
    if i:
        long_format = pd.concat([long_format, x])
    else:
        long_format = x        

long_format['ID'] = long_format['ID'].astype(str).str.zfill(3)
long_format['choice_word'] = long_format['choice']
long_format['choice'] = np.where(long_format['choice_word'] == 'Reference', 0, np.where(long_format['choice_word'] == 'Lottery', 1, np.nan))

In [11]:
participants = sorted(long_format['ID'].unique())
x0 = np.array([.12, -3.8,.76])
x1 = np.array([1, 0, 1])
x2 = np.array([7.59, 4.09, 4.99])
params = pd.DataFrame(columns=['ID', 'condition', 'alpha', 'beta', 'gamma', 'log_like', 'AIC', 'BIC', 'r^2', 'iterations', 'convergence'])
for part in participants:
    for t_label in ['safe', 'threat']:
        single_subject_data = long_format[long_format['ID'] == part]
        single_subject_data = single_subject_data[single_subject_data['block_type'] == t_label]
        if single_subject_data['choice'].isnull().sum():
            single_subject_data = single_subject_data.dropna(subset=['choice'])
        pd.set_option('display.max_rows', 500)
        bnds = Bounds([.11, -3.9, .5], [7.6, 4.16, 1000])
        res0 = minimize(cost, x0, bounds=bnds, options={'disp': True, 'maxiter': 1000})
        res1 = minimize(cost, x1, bounds=bnds, options={'disp': True, 'maxiter': 1000})
        res2 = minimize(cost, x2, bounds=bnds, options={'disp': True, 'maxiter': 1000})
        exec('optim = res%d' %np.argmin([res0.fun, res1.fun, res2.fun]))
        params.loc[part + '_' + t_label] = [part] + [t_label] + list(optim.x) + [optim.fun] + model_fit(optim.x, single_subject_data, optim.fun) + [optim.nit] + [optim.success]

long_pars = params.rename(index=str, columns={"alpha": "Value_alpha", "beta": "Value_beta", "gamma": "Value_gamma"})

long_pars = long_pars.reset_index()
g = sns.barplot(x="Parameter", y="Value", hue="condition", alpha=.6, capsize=.2, data=long_pars)
sns.stripplot(x="Parameter", y="Value", hue="condition", jitter=0.3, data=long_pars, dodge=True)
handles, labels = g.get_legend_handles_labels()
g.set_xticklabels(["$\\alpha$", "$\\beta$", "$\\gamma$"])

long_format['lotto_type'] = np.where(long_format.ambig > 0, 'Ambiguous', 'Risky')
money = np.linspace(0, 71, 1000)
if not os.path.exists('subjects'):
    os.mkdir('subjects')

for part in participants:
    part_data = long_format[long_format['ID'] == part]
    for t_label in part_data.block_type.unique():
        data = part_data[part_data.block_type == t_label]
        y_name = "P(Choose Lottery)"
        x_name = "Money"
        prob_name = "Prob"
        ambig_name = "Ambiguity"
        data = data.rename(index=str, columns={"choice": y_name, "val": x_name, 'prob': prob_name, 'ambig': ambig_name})
        risky = data[data.lotto_type == 'Risky']
        ambig = data[data.lotto_type == 'Ambiguous']
        fig, (ax0,ax1,ax2) = plt.subplots(nrows=3, ncols=2, figsize=(15,10), sharey='row')
        fig.suptitle('Participant: ' + part + ' ' + t_label.upper(), fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
        par_info = '$\\alpha$ = ' + "{:.3f}".format(params.loc[part + '_' + t_label].alpha) + '; ' + \
                   '$\\beta$ = ' + "{:.3f}".format(params.loc[part + '_' + t_label].beta) + '; ' + \
                   '$R^2$ = ' + "{:.3f}".format(params.loc[part + '_' + t_label]['r^2'])
        ax0[0].set_title(par_info)
        ax0[1].set_title(par_info)
        # Raw Data
        sns.scatterplot(x_name, y_name, data=risky[risky[prob_name]==.25], label=.25, ax=ax0[0], color=sns.color_palette("Blues", 3)[2])
        sns.scatterplot(x_name, y_name, data=risky[risky[prob_name]==.50], label=.50, ax=ax1[0], color=sns.color_palette("Blues", 3)[1])
        sns.scatterplot(x_name, y_name, data=risky[risky[prob_name]==.75], label=.75, ax=ax2[0], color=sns.color_palette("Blues", 3)[0])
        sns.scatterplot(x_name, y_name, data=ambig[ambig[ambig_name]==.24], label=.24, ax=ax0[1], color=sns.color_palette("Reds", 3)[0])
        sns.scatterplot(x_name, y_name, data=ambig[ambig[ambig_name]==.50], label=.50, ax=ax1[1], color=sns.color_palette("Reds", 3)[1])
        sns.scatterplot(x_name, y_name, data=ambig[ambig[ambig_name]==.74], label=.74, ax=ax2[1], color=sns.color_palette("Reds", 3)[2])
        par_info_full = '$\\alpha$ = ' + "{:.3f}".format(params.loc[part + '_' + t_label].alpha) + '; ' + \
                        '$\\beta$ = ' + "{:.3f}".format(params.loc[part + '_' + t_label].beta) + '; ' + \
                        '$\\gamma$ = ' + "{:.3f}".format(params.loc[part + '_' + t_label].gamma) + '; ' + \
                        '$R^2$ = ' + "{:.3f}".format(params.loc[part + '_' + t_label]['r^2']) + '; ' + \
                        'AIC = ' + "{:.3f}".format(params.loc[part + '_' + t_label].AIC) + '; ' + \
                        'BIC = ' + "{:.3f}".format(params.loc[part + '_' + t_label].BIC)
        fig.text(.99, .05, par_info_full, ha='right')
        fig.savefig(os.path.join(plot_dir, 'subjects', part + '_' + t_label.upper() + '_RAW.png'), format='png', dpi=300, transparent=True)

        
        # Sigmoid curves
        fig, ax = plt.subplots(nrows=1, ncols=2, figsize=(15,5), sharey='row')
        fig.suptitle('Participant: ' + part + ' ' + t_label.upper(), fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
        par_info = '$\\alpha$ = ' + "{:.3f}".format(params.loc[part + '_' + t_label].alpha) + '; ' + \
                   '$\\beta$ = ' + "{:.3f}".format(params.loc[part + '_' + t_label].beta) + '; ' + \
                   '$R^2$ = ' + "{:.3f}".format(params.loc[part + '_' + t_label]['r^2'])
        ax[0].set_title(par_info)
        ax[1].set_title(par_info)
        # Risky Prediction
        A = 0
        df = pd.DataFrame(columns=['money', 'predict', 'prob'])
        for p in [.75, .5, .25]: # Hard coded because I wanted it in a specific order
            predict = choice_predict(params.loc[part + "_" + t_label].alpha, 
                                     params.loc[part + "_" + t_label].beta, 
                                     params.loc[part + "_" + t_label].gamma, 
                                     np.repeat(p, money.shape), 
                                     np.repeat(A, money.shape), 
                                     money)
            df = df.append(pd.DataFrame({'money': money, 'predict': predict, 'prob': np.repeat(p, money.shape)}))

        sns.lineplot(x='money', y='predict', hue='prob', data=df, palette=sns.color_palette("Blues", 3), ax=ax[0], legend=False)

        # Ambiguity Prediction
        p = .5
        df = pd.DataFrame(columns=['money', 'predict', 'ambig'])
        for A in [.24, .5, .74]:
            predict = choice_predict(params.loc[part + "_" + t_label].alpha, 
                                     params.loc[part + "_" + t_label].beta, 
                                     params.loc[part + "_" + t_label].gamma, 
                                     np.repeat(p, money.shape), 
                                     np.repeat(A, money.shape), 
                                     money)
            df = df.append(pd.DataFrame({'money': money, 'predict': predict, 'ambig': np.repeat(A, money.shape)}))

        sns.lineplot(x='money', y='predict', hue='ambig', data=df, palette=sns.color_palette("Reds", 3), ax=ax[1], legend=False)

        # Plot data ontop
        sns.scatterplot(x=x_name, y=y_name, hue=prob_name, data=risky, palette=sns.color_palette("Blues", 3), ax=ax[0])
        ax[0].legend(bbox_to_anchor=(.9, .5), loc="center left", borderaxespad=0.)
        sns.scatterplot(x=x_name, y=y_name, hue=ambig_name, data=ambig, palette=sns.color_palette("Reds", 3), ax=ax[1])
        ax[1].legend(bbox_to_anchor=(.9, .5), loc="center left", borderaxespad=0.)
        fig.text(.99, -.05, par_info_full, ha='right')
        fig.savefig(os.path.join(plot_dir, 'subjects', part + '_' + t_label.upper() + '.png'), format='png', dpi=300, transparent=True, bbox_inches="tight")
